# Extraction Contracts

- Extract into typed intermediate JSON packets, never straight into canonical entities.
- Keep packet fields source-backed and normalization-friendly.
- Models should suggest candidates, claims, contexts, metrics, and ambiguities.
- Canonical ID assignment, synonym resolution, unit normalization, and merges are deterministic post-processing steps.
- Add new packet fields only when they serve downstream normalization or curation.
- If packets include source-backed usefulness, limitation, prerequisite, or alternative prose, preserve that evidence through normalization/materialization and surface it with provenance instead of regenerating generic UI copy later.
